Line bottom and sides of 8x8x1-inch or 1-1/2-quart baking dish with Vanilla Wafers. Combine pudding mix, milk, and margarine in saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Remove from heat. Layer slices of banana over Vanilla Wafers, then add a layer of pudding. Repeat layers of Vanilla Wafers, bananas, and pudding. Chill until firm, about 3 hours. Serve with whipped topping and garnish with banana slices. Banana pudding may also be layered in individual dessert glasses or dishes.